               <msContents>
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i1">
                     <rubric>Nomina sacra; elements of the punctuation signs and of the text dividers; elements of the Ethiopic numerals.&#xD;
&#xD;
Two lines on the incipit column of Text I-2, alternating with black lines; two initial lines of Texts I-1, I-3 and each miracle of Text I-4; first one or two words of each strophe of Text I-5.</rubric>
                     <incipit>
                        <foreign xml:lang="en"/>
                     </incipit>
                     <explicit>
                        <foreign xml:lang="en"/>
                     </explicit>
                     <note/>
                  </msItem>
                  <!--The data in the items below refers to other items. please remove this items and move the information to the appropriate place.-->
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i2">
                     <note>All the miracles are numbered. The numbers 50, 81 and 87 were not used, the numbers 65, 80 and 88 were used twice.</note>
                     <note>The 1st miracle is followed by the hymn: Sobä ṣäḥafä Däqsǝyos täʾamriha ʿǝludä ... "When Däqsǝyos wrote the collection of her miracles ..." (fol. 8rb, ls. 7-11).</note>
                     <note>Text II-5 comprises 32 strophes which are strophes 1-32 according to GrohHymn pp. 336-53.</note>
                  </msItem>
               </msContents>
